The River actress Galaletsang Koffman has finally undergone corrective eye surgery after she had been wearing glasses for 25 years. Eye surgery or laser vision correction is a type of refractive surgery for the correction of myopia, hyperopia, and an actual cure for astigmatism in the cornea. Galaletsang is known for her fun and bubbly role, Beauty, on The River on 1Magic. The actress shared that she had her surgery three weeks ago and is currently recovering. “After 25 years of wearing spectacles, I finally underwent corrective surgery. It has been three weeks since my surgery,” she wrote.  For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.